CXR (11/15/3050): No focal consolidation, effusion, or pneumothorax. Heart size upper limit of normal.
CT Head (11/15/3050): Chronic microvascular ischemic changes. No acute hemorrhage, mass effect, or midline shift.

Assessment and Plan: 
82 y.o. female from SNF with history of dementia and CKD presenting with fever, tachycardia, and acute encephalopathy. Labs and clinical picture are highly suggestive of Sepsis secondary to Urinary Tract Infection (Urosepsis).

#Sepsis / Urinary Tract Infection
Patient meets SIRS and qSOFA criteria. UA is grossly positive. 
- Source: Likely UTI/Urosepsis.
- Coverage: Patient received Vancomycin and Ceftriaxone in ED. Given PCN allergy (rash), will transition to Aztreonam 1g IV q12h (adjusted for renal function) and discontinue Vanc/Ceftriaxone once stable. 
- Cultures: Awaiting urine and blood culture sensitivities.
- Mentation: Likely metabolic/infectious encephalopathy. Will monitor for improvement as infection clears.

#Acute Kidney Injury on CKD
Cr elevated to 1.92 from baseline 1.2. Likely pre-renal component due to sepsis/dehydration.
- IVF: Continue maintenance IVF with D5 1/2NS at 75cc/hr. Monitor I/Os closely.
- Meds: Hold Lisinopril and Metformin. Avoid nephrotoxins.

#Atrial Fibrillation
Irregularly irregular on exam. 
- Rate control: Continue Metoprolol Succinate 25mg PO Daily; monitor HR/BP.
- Anticoagulation: Continue home Apixaban 2.5mg BID (noted age/weight/Cr for dosing).

#Altered Mental Status (Encephalopathy)
Multifactorial (Infection, AKI, possible dehydration).
- CT Head negative for acute stroke.
- Monitor neuro checks q4h.
- Fall precautions.

#Chronic Medical Issues
- Vascular Dementia: Continue home Memantine and Donepezil.
- Hypertension: Hold Lisinopril for now given borderline BPs and AKI.
- Stage 1 Sacral Decubitus: Barrier cream, frequent repositioning.

Hospital Bundle
Diet: NPO (due to somnolence) - reassess for speech/swallow eval in AM.
DVT Prophylaxis: Continue Apixaban.
Telemetry: Yes, for Afib and tachycardia.
Dispo: Pending resolution of infection and return to baseline mentation.

CODE: Full Code
